                <note rend="inline" type="source">884.6461 Tsana Dam/115: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ethiopia (<persName type="from"
                            >Southard</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-09-21T18:00:00+02:35"
                            >September 21, 1929—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 21—8:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>30. Referring to my cable September 19, 9 p.m. The King has now informed me that
                    the White Corporation representative to the conference should arrive here at any
                    time during the last 10 days of December. I am informed by the British Minister
                    that the King has not yet notified <pb facs="0969" n="865" xml:id="pg_865"/> him
                    of the acceptance of the British proposal for a conference but I anticipate that
                    such action will occur within a few days<note n="14" xml:id="d641fn14">In
                        telegram No. 32, September 25, 6 p.m., the Minister in Ethiopia reported
                        that notification of the King’s acceptance was given on September 24
                        (884.6461 Tsana Dam/118).</note> and that the delay has no special
                    significance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Southard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
